On the evening of March 12, Beijing time, la Liga officials said: "Due to the isolation of the real team and other club-related players, La Liga believes that measures to combat the new pneumonia should be further improved. ". Therefore, pursuant to section 664 of the RCA, it has been agreed to suspend at least the next two rounds of La Liga and La Liga. We will re-evaluate the situation when the quarantine period for the affected clubs expires."

In less than a day, La Liga and La Liga have been suspended from their original "empty ground" . The immediate cause was a situation at Real Madrid.

Real Madrid basketball player Trey Thompkins, who tested positive for the new coronavirus, has been quarantined, reports Channel 6 and Maka. Last week, the Real Madrid basketball team went to Milan for an open match.

As potential contacts, the Real Madrid football and basketball teams, which are based at the Baldebebas training ground, have been evacuated for two weeks. The staff involved are among them.

Real Madrid confirmed the incident in an official announcement, but did not mention the specific players affected. Predictably, the galacticos'second leg against Manchester City in the Champions League quarter-final on March 17 will also be postponed due to exceptional circumstances.

Currently, all five major European Leagues have responded to the outbreak with an emergency: Serie A and La Liga suspended for a month and two weeks, respectively; Fußball-Bundesliga and Ligue 1 in open play mode; and the Premier League, where infection figures are strictly enforced, it is likely that there will be no cheering matches this weekend, either.

Just after La Liga suspended the first two leagues, Spanish media said UEFA was considering suspending the Champions League and UEFA Cup tie on the same day rather than playing in an empty ground.

Before that, juventus have announced: "The team's player Danyll Rugani has tested positive for the new coronavirus, there are no symptoms of pneumonia. ". The Club has initiated quarantine procedures in accordance with the law for the player and associated contacts."

Since then, inter, who had just finished Serie A with Clube Atlético Juventus, were quick to add: "after the Juventus F.C. confirmed that Rugani had been diagnosed with Covid-19, Inter football club hereby suspended all sporting activities until further notice. The club is now taking action and taking all necessary measures."

As the CLUBE ATLÉTICO Juventus has not released the sampling time, his close contact range of up to, is not yet confirmed. What is certain is that Rugani was at Clube Atlético Juventus's team practice two days ago.

On the morning of March 12, Beijing time, "You may have seen the news, " Rugani wrote on social media. "I want to reassure anyone who is worried about me. I am fine. I ask you to follow the rules, because this virus does not discriminate. We want to thank you for ourselves, for our loved ones, and for those around us. "

According to Tuttosport, Rugani's teammate, Ronaldo, who is still in Madeira, issued a statement calling for the suspension of all world sporting events in response to the spread of the outbreak. There are unconfirmed reports that Cristiano Ronaldo has been tested twice and both results have been negative.
